
[1]prosopopy

   PROS'OPOPY, n. [Gr. perso, and to make.] A figure in rhetoric by which
   things are represented as persons, or by which things inanimate are
   spoken of as animated beings, or by which an absent person is
   introduced as speaking, or a deceased person is represented as alive
   and present. It includes personification, but is more extensive in its
   signification.
